      <section id="security-isolation">
        <h2>4. Zero-Trust Security & Row-Level Access Control</h2>
        <p>
          Deploying autonomous AI agents in production requires establishing rigorous guardrails. When building custom MCP servers at **N3 Global Tech**, we enforce a zero-trust architectural model:
        </p>
        <p>
          First, database connection pools utilized by MCP servers are configured with dedicated, low-privilege database roles governed by **PostgreSQL Row-Level Security (RLS)** policies. Even if an LLM is manipulated via prompt injection into requesting cross-tenant data, the database engine enforces tenant boundaries at the silicon level. Second, mutating tools require human-in-the-loop (HITL) approval tokens before transaction execution.
        </p>
      </section>

